what is LVM in linux?
in Linux, Logical Volume Manager (LVM) is a device mapper target that provides logical volume management for the Linux kernel. 
what is it's benefit?
volumes with LVM can be resized ,moved
-for large volumes you can mange the volume as groups rather than using sda1 sda2 ,.... you can use "developing","sales" and this give you top-view of storage-volume 

