what is the benefit of LVM in large system?
it's a good way with many disk drives cause managing it is a time consuming job,
you can allocate specific volumes to groups ...ha ha ha :) .... so what i can do if i add a new derive?
ok ... rather than transfer the groups content to the new hard-disk ==> you can can add the new disk to groups so ,groups can extend
